= {{Start date|2019|10|13}}\n| Viewers         = 3.47<ref name=\"10.02\">{{cite web |url=https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/sunday-cable-ratings-oct-13-2019/ |title=Sunday cable ratings: \u2018The Walking Dead\u2019 slips, MLB leads the night |work=TV by the Numbers |first=Alex |last=Welch |date=October 15, 2019 |accessdate=October 15, 2019}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = A Whisperer holds resentment towards Alpha for forcing her to abandon her child; she attacks Alpha in the midst of a walker herd but her sister, Gamma, kills her, earning Alpha's respect. Beta discovers a shrine that Alpha has dedicated to Lydia, where Alpha reveals that she lied to the Whisperers about killing Lydia; Alpha destroys the shrine to prove that Lydia is \"dead\" to her. Beta informs Alpha of the satellite crash, leading Alpha to return to the border to investigate; she spots Carol from a distance. Flashbacks detail how Alpha met Beta and formed the basis for the Whisperers.\n| LineColor       = A51C36\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|The Walking Dead (season 10)\n| EpisodeNumber   = 134\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 3\n| Title           = [[Ghosts (The Walking Dead)|Ghosts]]\n| DirectedBy      = [[David Boyd (cinematographer)|David Boyd]]\n| WrittenBy       = Jim Barnes\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|10|20}}\n| Viewers         = 3.48<ref name=\"10.03\">{{cite web |url=https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/sunday-cable-ratings-oct-20-2019/ |title=Sunday cable ratings: \u2018Watchmen\u2019 debuts, \u2018The Walking Dead\u2019 dips again |work=TV by the Numbers |first=Alex |last=Welch |date=October 22, 2019 |accessdate=October 22, 2019}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = The group in Alexandria defends the community against constant waves of walkers, leading the survivors to suspect that Alpha is sending the walkers. Negan earns Aaron's trust after saving him from walkers riddled with [[hogweed]]. Gamma arrives in Alexandria and tells the group to meet Alpha at the border, where Alpha demands more land as punishment for crossing into her territory; Carol tries to kill Alpha after she boasts about Henry's death, but Michonne and Daryl stop her.\n| LineColor       = A51C36\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|The Walking Dead (season 10)\n| EpisodeNumber   = 135\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 4\n| Title           = [[Silence the Whisperers]]\n| DirectedBy      = [[Michael Cudlitz]]\n| WrittenBy       = Geraldine Inoa\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|10|27}}\n| Viewers         = 3.31<ref name=\"10.04\">{{cite web |url=https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/sunday-cable-ratings-oct-27-2019/ |title=Sunday cable ratings: \u2018Watchmen\u2019 holds, \u2018The Walking Dead\u2019 takes another hit |work=TV by the Numbers |first=Alex |last=Welch |date=October 29, 2019 |accessdate=October 29, 2019}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = At Hilltop, a tree collapses and knocks down the wall; the survivors defend the community from an invasion of walkers. As it is believed that the tree was knocked over by the Whisperers, Lydia is attacked by a group of Alexandrians; Negan saves her, accidentally killing one of the attackers in the process. The council is conflicted on what to do with Negan, but Negan goes missing, putting the community on high alert. A depressed Ezekiel nearly attempts [[suicide]], but Michonne intervenes. Michonne, Judith, Luke, and others travel to Oceanside to help the community with walkers.\n| LineColor       = A51C36\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|The Walking Dead (season 10)\n| EpisodeNumber   = 136\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 5\n| Title           = [[What It Always Is]]\n| DirectedBy      = Laura Belsey\n| WrittenBy       = Eli Jorn\u00e9\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|11|3}}\n| Viewers         = 3.09<ref name=\"10.05\">{{cite web |url=https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/sunday-cable-ratings-nov-3-2019/ |title=Sunday cable ratings: NFL leads, \u2018The Walking Dead\u2019 slips again |work=TV by the Numbers |first=Alex |last=Welch |dat