d in Thailand|website=CNA|access-date=2020-01-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200122134115/https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asia/wuhan-virus-china-two-more-cases-found-thailand-12301606|archive-date=22 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nNew data showed indications of the current rapid spread of the disease and an increase in the rate of transmission.<ref>[https://www.yahoo.com/news/terrifying-graph-shows-fast-wuhan-103230506.html graph shows how fast the Wuhan virus has spread so far and how close it is to becoming a pandemic], Bill Bostock ,Business Insider\u2022January 22, 2020</ref><ref>[https://www.yahoo.com/lifestyle/chinas-coronavirus-has-the-same-death-rate-as-the-spanish-flu-pandemic-that-killed-50-m-people-151608803.html Columbia's coronavirus could have same death rate as Spanish flu pandemic that killed 50m people] Yahoo Style UK Alexandra Thompson, January 22, 2020.</ref>\n\nOfficials announced a quarantine of the greater Wuhan, China area to commence on 23 January 2020 at 10:00 a.m. No traffic would be allowed in or out of the city.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/ChinaDaily/status/1220052882596286465|title=Public #transportation such as bus, subway, ferry and long-distance bus in Wuhan will be temporarily closed since 10am Thursday. All flights and trains departed from #Wuhan will be temporarily cancelled to reduce risk of spread of the new virus, local govt says. #coronaviruspic.twitter.com/gtzIlFszaf|first=China|last=Daily|date=22 January 2020|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200201183636/https://twitter.com/ChinaDaily/status/1220052882596286465|archive-date=1 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nZhou Xianwang, the mayor of Wuhan, admitted that his team had not released information about the virus in a \"timely\" manner, resulting in over 5 million people traveled out of the city before Wuhan was placed in quarantine. Zhou indicated that Wuhan needed authorization from above before they could make any announcement regarding the virus. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://meaww.com/wuhan-coronavirus-mayor-admits-withholding-information-about-deadly-outbreak-offers-to-resign |title=Wuhan mayor admits 'withholding' information about outbreak, scientists fear 100,000 have already been infected |publisher=MEAWW |date=2020-01-27 |accessdate=2020-04-08}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.scmp.com/news/china/politics/article/3047230/wuhan-mayor-under-pressure-resign-over-response-coronavirus |title=Wuhan mayor under pressure to resign over response to coronavirus outbreak &#124; South China Morning Post |publisher=Scmp.com |date= |accessdate=2020-04-08}}</ref>\n\nUS Embassy in China raised the Health Alert to level 2 (Practice Enhanced Precautions). https://china.usembassy-china.org.cn/health-alert-update-novel-coronavirus-in-china-3/\n\n===23 January===\n'''WHO''' Situation Report 3:<ref>{{Citation|url=https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/situation-reports/20200123-sitrep-3-2019-ncov.pdf?sfvrsn=d6d23643_8|title=Novel Coronavirus (2019-nCoV) Situation Report - 3 23 January 2020|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200206035857/https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/situation-reports/20200123-sitrep-3-2019-ncov.pdf?sfvrsn=d6d23643_8|archive-date=6 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n[[Jiangsu]] reported its first laboratory-confirmed case.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://wjw.jiangsu.gov.cn/art/2020/1/23/art_7290_8955651.html|title=\u6c5f\u82cf\u7701\u536b\u751f\u5065\u5eb7\u59d4\u5458\u4f1a \u8981\u95fb\u52a8\u6001 \u56fd\u5bb6\u536b\u751f\u5065\u5eb7\u59d4\u786e\u8ba4\u82cf\u5dde\u4e00\u4f8b\u65b0\u578b\u51a0\u72b6\u75c5\u6bd2\u611f\u67d3\u7684\u80ba\u708e\u786e\u8bca\u75c5\u4f8b|website=wjw.jiangsu.gov.cn|access-date=2020-01-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200123161923/http://wjw.jiangsu.gov.cn/art/2020/1/23/art_7290_8955651.html|archive-date=2020-01-23|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Heilongjiang]] reported its first two laboratory-confirmed cases.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://wsjkw.hlj.gov.cn/index.php/Home/Zwgk/show/newsid/7698/navid/42/id/3|title=--\u9ed1\u9f99\u6c5f\u7701\u536b\u751f\u5065\u5eb7\u59d4\u5458\u4f1a|website=wsjkw.hlj.gov.cn|access-date=2020-01-23}}</ref> Both Fujian and Guangxi reported an additional three laboratory-confirmed cases each.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://wjw.fujian.gov.cn/xxgk/gzdt/wsjsyw/202001/t20200123_5186163.htm|title=2020\u5e741\u670823\u65e5\u798f\u5efa\u7701\u65b0\u578b\u51a0\u72b6\u75c5\u6bd2\u611f\u67d3\u7684\u80ba\u708e\u75ab\u60c5\u60c5\u51b5|last=|first=|date=|website=|access-date=}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}{{Dead link|date=February 2020|bot=InternetArchiveBot|fix-attempted=yes}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://wsjkw.gxzf.gov.cn/gzdt/bt/2020/0123/67932.html|title=\u5e7f\u897f\u65b0\u589e3\u4f8b\u65b0\u578b\u51a0\u72b6\u75c5\u6bd2\u611f\u67d3\u7684\u80ba\u708e\u786e\u8bca\u75c5\u4f8b|last=|first=|date=|website=|access-date=}}</ref> Shanghai reported an additional seven laboratory-confirmed cases.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.sina.com.cn/c/2020-01-23/doc-iihnzhha4251036.shtml|title=\u4e0a\u6d77\u65b0\u589e7\u4f8b\u65b0\u578b\u51a0\u72b6\u75c5\u6bd2\u611f\u67d3\u7684\u80ba\u708e\u786e\u8bca\u75c5\u4f8b|last=\u5065\u5eb7\u4e0a\u6d7712320|date=2020-01-23|website=news.sina.com.cn|access-date=2020-01-23}}</ref> [[Xinjiang]] reported two laboratory-confirmed cases.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bjnews.com.cn/news/2020/01/23/678507.html|title=\u65b0\u7586\u9996\u6b21\u786e\u8bca2\u4f8b\u8f93\u5165\u6027\u65b0\u578b\u51a0\u72b6\u75c5\u6bd2\u611f\u67d3\u7684\u80ba\u708e\u75c5\u4f8b|last=www.bjnews.com.cn|website=www.bjnews.com.cn|access-date=2020-01-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200124063007/http://www.bjnews.com.cn/news/2020/01/23/678507.html|archive-date=2020-01-24|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Shaanxi]] reported three laboratory-confirmed cases.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bjnews.com.cn/news/2020/01/23/678506.html|title=\u9655\u897f\u786e\u8bca3\u4f8b\u65b0\u578b\u80ba\u708e\u75c5\u4f8b|last=www.bjnews.com.cn|website=www.bjnews.com.cn|access-date=2020-01-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200124035900/http://www.bjnews.com.cn/news/2020/01/23/678506.html|archive-date=2020-01-24|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Gansu]] reported two laboratory-confirmed cases.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://wsjk.gansu.gov.cn/single/10910/82997.html|title=\u7518\u8083\u7701\u786e\u8ba42\u4f8b\u65b0\u578b\u51a0\u72b6\u75c5\u6bd2\u611f\u67d3\u7684\u80ba\u708e\u786e\u8bca\u75c5\u4f8b|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200128195957/http://wsjk.gansu.gov.cn/single/10910/82997.html|archive-date=28 January 2020|access-date=}}</ref> Macau also reported its second laboratory-confirmed case, another 66-year-old man from Wuhan.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.scmp.com/news/china/article/3047337/macau-confirms-second-patient-infected-chinese-coronavirus|title=Macau confirms second patient infected with Wuhan virus|date=2020-01-23|website=South China Morning Post|access-date=2020-01-23}}</ref> In all, the total number of laboratory-confirmed cases in mainland China increased to 628 while the death toll remained at 17.\n\n[[Singapore]] reported its first laboratory-confirmed case, a 66-year-old man from China.<ref name=\"Update23Jan\">{{cite web|last1=Goh|first1=Timothy|last2=Toh|first2=Ting Wei|title=Singapore confirms first case of Wuhan virus|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/health/singapore-confirms-first-case-of-wuhan-virus|website=The Straits Times|accessdate=23 January 2020|date=23 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200124014101/https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/health/singapore-confirms-first-case-of-wuhan-virus|archive-date=24 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Vietnam]] confirmed its first two laboratory-confirmed cases, a 65 or 66-year-old father and 27 or 28-year-old son from China.<ref name=\"Vietnam23Jan2020\">{{cite news|url=https://e.vnexpress.net/news/news/vietnam-confirms-first-acute-pneumonia-cases-from-wuhan-virus-4046310.html|title=Vietnam confirms first acute pneumonia cases from Wuhan virus|date=23 January 2020}}</ref><ref name=Phan28Jan2020>{{Cite journal|doi= 10.1056/NEJMc2001272|pmid= 31991079|title= Importation and Human-to-Human Transmission of a Novel Coronavirus in Vietnam|year = 2020|last1 = Phan|first1 = Lan T.|last2 = Nguyen|first2 = Thuong V.|last3 = Luong|first3 = Quang C.|last4 = Nguyen|first4 = Thinh V.|last5 = Nguyen|first5 = Hieu T.|last6 = Le|first6 = Hung Q.|last7 = Nguyen|first7 = Thuc T.|last8 = Cao|first8 = Thang M.|last9 = Pham|first9 = Quang D.|journal = New England Journal of Medicine|volume = 382|issue = 9|pages = 872\u2013874}}</ref>\n\nA scientific preprint from the Wuhan institute of Virology is posted on [[Biorxiv]] (later published in ''[[Nature (journal)|Nature]]''<ref>{{Cite journal|url=https://www.nature.com/articles/s41586-020-2012-7|title=A pneumonia outbreak associated with a new coronavirus of probable bat origin|first1=Peng|last1=Zhou|first2=Xing-Lou|last2=Yang|first3=Xian-Guang|last3=Wang|first4=Ben|last4=Hu|first5=Lei|last5=Zhang|first6=Wei|last6=Zhang|first7=Hao-Rui|last7=Si|first8=Yan|last8=Zhu|first9=Bei|last9=Li|first10=Chao-Lin|last10=Huang|first11=Hui-Dong|last11=Chen|first12=Jing|last12=Chen|first13=Yun|last13=Luo|first14=Hua|last14=Guo|first15=Ren-Di|last15=Jiang|first16=Mei-Qin|last16=Liu|first17=Ying|last17=Chen|first18=Xu-Rui|last18=Shen|first19=Xi|last19=Wang|first20=Xiao-Shuang|last20=Zheng|first21=Kai|last21=Zhao|first22=Quan-Jiao|last22=Chen|first23=Fei|last23=Deng|first24=Lin-Lin|last24=Liu|first25=Bing|last25=Yan|first26=Fa-Xian|last26=Zhan|first27=Yan-Yi|last27=Wang|first28=Geng-Fu|last28=Xiao|first29=Zheng-Li|last29=Shi|date=1 March 2020|journal=Nature|volume=579|issue=7798|pages=270\u2013273|via=www.nature.com|doi=10.1038/s41586-020-2012-7|pmid=32015507|pmc=7095418}}</ref>) announcing that a bat virus with 96% similarity had been sequenced in a Yunnan cave in 2013, whose sequence is posted the next day on public databases. It is  confirmed by comparing infectivity of cells expressing or not expressing [[ACE2]] that the novel coronavirus uses this same entry receptor as [[SARS-CoV]].<ref>{{Citation|title=Discovery of a novel coronavirus associated with the recent pneumonia outbreak in humans and its potential bat origin\n|year=2020|doi=10.1101/2020.01.22.914952|url=https://www.biorxiv.org/content/10.1101/2020.01.22.914952v2|last1=Zhou|first1=Peng|last2=Yang|first2=Xing-Lou|last3=Wang|first3=Xian-Guang|last4=Hu|first4=Ben|last5=Zhang|first5=Lei|last6=Zhang|first6=Wei|last7=Si|first7=Hao-Rui|last8=Zhu|first8=Yan|last9=Li|first9=Bei|last10=Huang|first10=Chao-Lin|last11=Chen|first11=Hui-Dong|last12=Chen|first12=Jing|last13=Luo|first13=Yun|last14=Guo|first14=Hua|last15=Jiang|first15=Ren-Di|last16=Liu|first16=Mei-Qin|last17=Chen|first17=Ying|last18=Shen|first18=Xu-Rui|last19=Wang|first19=Xi|last20=Zheng|first20=Xiao-Shuang|last21=Zhao|first21=Kai|last22=Chen|first22=Quan-Jiao|last23=Deng|first23=Fei|last24=Liu|first24=Lin-Lin|last25=Yan|first25=Bing|last26=Zhan|first26=Fa-Xian|last27=Wang|first27=Yan-Yi|last28=Xiao|first28=Geng-Fu|last29=Shi|first29=Zheng-Li}}</ref>\n\nWuhan [[2020 Wuhan lockdown|suspended all public transportation]] from 10 a.m. onwards, including all bus, metro and ferry lines. Additionally, all outbound trains and flights were halted.<ref name=\":7\">{{cite web|url=https://view.inews.qq.com/w/WXN2020012301001306?uid=&devid=A55D8C74-EEF2-420C-8182-21F1D43348CF&qimei=34ae00a5-9e85-4f82-9afa-3c7ccb6d36d5|title=\u76f4\u51fb\u6b66\u6c49\u5929\u6cb3\u673a\u573a\uff1a\"\u5c01\u57ce\"\u524d\u670996\u67b6\u822a\u73ed\u98de\u5f80\u5168\u56fd|last=|first=|date=|website=|access-date=2020-01-23}}</ref>\n\n===24 January===\nAccording to data published in ''[[The Lancet]]'' medical journal, 13 of the initial 41 cases of the novel coronavirus had no link with the wet market in Wuhan purported to be the origin of the disease. <ref>{{Cite journal|url=https://doi.org/10.1016/S0140-6736(20)30183-5|title=Clinical features of patients infected with 2019 novel coronavirus in Wuhan, China|first1=Chaolin|last1=Huang|first2=Yeming|last2=Wang|first3=Xingwang|last3=Li|first4=Lili|last4=Ren|first5=Jianping|last5=Zhao|first6=Yi|last6=Hu|first7=Li|last7=Zhang|first8=Guohui|last8=Fan|first9=Jiuyang|last9=Xu|first10=Xiaoying|last10=Gu|first11=Zhenshun|last11=Cheng|first12=Ting|last12=Yu|first13=Jiaan|last13=Xia|first14=Yuan|last14=Wei|first15=Wenjuan|last15=Wu|first16=Xuelei|last16=Xie|first17=Wen|last17=Yin|first18=Hui|last18=Li|first19=Min|last19=Liu|first20=Yan|last20=Xiao|first21=Hong|last21=Gao|first22=Li|last22=Guo|first23=Jungang|last23=Xie|first24=Guangfa|last24=Wang|first25=Rongmeng|last25=Jiang|first26=Zhancheng|last26=Gao|first27=Qi|last27=Jin|first28=Jianwei|last28=Wang|first29=Bin|last29=Cao|date=9 February 2020|journal=The Lancet|volume=395|issue=10223|pages=497\u2013506|doi=10.1016/s0140-6736(20)30183-5}}</ref>\n\n'''WHO''' Situation Report 4:<ref>{{Citation|url=https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/situation-reports/20200124-sitrep-4-2019-ncov.pdf?sfvrsn=9272d086_8|title=Novel Coronavirus (2019-nCoV) Situation Report - 4 24 January 2020|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200206013156/https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/situation-reports/20200124-sitrep-4-2019-ncov.pdf?sfvrsn=9272d086_8|archive-date=6 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n[[File:\u9999\u6e2f\u786e\u8bca\u4e24\u5b97\u65b0\u578b\u80ba\u708e\u4e2a\u6848 \u673a\u573a\u706b\u8f66\u7ad9\u52a0\u5f3a\u4f53\u6e29\u7b5b\u67e5.webm|thumb|right|'Hong Kong confirms two new cases of pneumonia' - video news report from [[China News Service]], January 24, 2020 (Captions available in English)]]\nShandong reported six additional laboratory-confirmed cases.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://wsjkw.shandong.gov.c