0|website=Al Jazeera|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200128191934/https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/01/china-battles-coronavirus-outbreak-latest-updates-200124063503577.html|archive-date=January 28, 2020|access-date=}}</ref> France reported its first three confirmed cases, the first occurrences in the EU.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.sky.com/story/coronavirus-outbreak-hospital-to-be-built-in-five-days-as-death-toll-rises-in-china-11916211|title=Coronavirus outbreak: First confirmed cases in Europe as France declares three infections|last=|first=|date=|website=Sky News|access-date=24 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.lemonde.fr/planete/article/2020/01/24/coronavirus-deux-premiers-cas-confirmes-en-france-a-bordeaux-et-paris_6027158_3244.html|title=Coronavirus : un troisi\u00e8me cas d'infection confirm\u00e9 en France|last=|first=|date=24 January 2020|work=Le Monde.fr|access-date=24 January 2020|language=fr}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.lefigaro.fr/sciences/coronavirus-trois-premiers-cas-confirmes-en-france-20200124|title=Coronavirus: trois premiers cas confirm\u00e9s en France|last1=Jacob|first1=Etienne|date=24 January 2020|work=Le Figaro.fr|language=fr}}</ref> The French Health Minister [[Agn\u00e8s Buzyn]] stated that it is likely other cases would arise in the country.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.trust.org//item/20200124190017-e8ycd/|title=France declares first two confirmed cases of coronavirus|last=|first=|date=24 January 2020|website=Reuters|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nThe first confirmed incidence of human-to-human transmission outside of China was documented by the WHO in Vietnam.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/situation-reports/20200124-sitrep-4-2019-ncov.pdf?sfvrsn=9272d086_2|title=Novel Coronavirus (2019-nCoV) SITUATION REPORT - 4|last=|first=|date=January 24, 2020|website=World Health Organization|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200125232652/https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/situation-reports/20200124-sitrep-4-2019-ncov.pdf?sfvrsn=9272d086_2|archive-date=January 25, 2020|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nA study by Chinese researchers indicates that people can be symptom-free for several days while the coronavirus is incubating, increasing the risk of contagious infection without forewarning signs.<ref name=\"auto1\" />\n\nA consortium of Chinese medical experts charged by the Chinese CDC with investigating the inception of the virus published their report in ''[[The Lancet]]'', reporting details of 41 first known patients.<ref name=Wang24Jan2020>{{Cite journal|url=https://www.thelancet.com/journals/lancet/article/PIIS0140-6736(20)30185-9/abstract|title=A novel coronavirus outbreak of global health concern|first1=Chen|last1=Wang|first2=Peter W.|last2=Horby|first3=Frederick G.|last3=Hayden|first4=George F.|last4=Gao|date=24 January 2020|journal=The Lancet|volume=0|issue=10223|pages=470\u2013473|via=www.thelancet.com|doi=10.1016/S0140-6736(20)30185-9|pmid=31986257}}</ref>\n\nBy the end of the day, the entire Hubei province had gone under a city-by-city quarantine, apart from [[Xiangyang]] and [[Shennongjia|Shennongjia Forestry District]].\n\n===25 January===\n[[Communist Party of China|Chinese Communist Party]] [[General Secretary of the Communist Party of China|general secretary]] [[Xi Jinping]] called the \"accelerating spread\" of the coronavirus a \"grave situation\" in a [[Politburo of the Communist Party of China|Party Politburo]] meeting,<ref name=\"People's Daily Online\">{{cite news|url=http://en.people.cn/n3/2020/0125/c90000-9651799.html|title=CPC leadership meets to discuss novel coronavirus prevention, control|date=25 January 2020|work=People's Daily Online|quote=Xi Jinping, general secretary of the CPC Central Committee, chaired the meeting.|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200125202946/http://en.people.cn/n3/2020/0125/c90000-9651799.html|archive-date=25 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> and that it was \"mutating\" as Beijing escalates measures to contain the illness.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/asia/coronavirus-news-china-new-year-latest-wuhan-symptoms-virus-uk-france-australia-jinping-a9302011.html|title=Spread of coronavirus 'accelerating', warns China president|date=25 January 2020|website=The Independent|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200204232255/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/asia/coronavirus-news-china-new-year-latest-wuhan-symptoms-virus-uk-france-australia-jinping-a9302011.html|archive-date=4 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n'''WHO''' Situation Report 5:<ref>{{Citation|url=https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/situation-reports/20200125-sitrep-5-2019-ncov.pdf?sfvrsn=429b143d_8|title=Novel Coronavirus (2019-nCoV) Situation Report - 5 25 January 2020|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200206035857/https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/situation-reports/20200125-sitrep-5-2019-ncov.pdf?sfvrsn=429b143d_8|archive-date=6 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nAustralia confirmed its first four cases, one in [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://7news.com.au/news/health/first-australian-coronavirus-case-confirmed-in-victoria-c-664530|title=First Australian coronavirus case confirmed in Victoria|last=Daoud|first=Elizabeth|date=January 25, 2020|website=7 News|access-date=}}</ref> and three in [[New South Wales]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/science/2020/jan/25/coronavirus-five-people-in-nsw-being-tested-for-deadly-disease\n|title=Coronavirus: three cases in NSW and one in Victoria as infection reaches Australia|last=Doherty|first=Ben|work=The Guardian|date=25 January 2020|access-date=25 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.smh.com.au/national/victoria/coronavirus-case-confirmed-in-victoria-20200125-p53unk.html\n|title=Coronavirus spreads across Australia amid scramble to find more cases|last2=McCauley|first2=Dana|last1=Cunningham|first1=Melissa|work=Sydney Morning Herald|date=25 January 2020|access-date=25 January 2020}}</ref> Malaysia reported its first three cases in [[Johor Bahru]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asia/wuhan-virus-malaysia-confirms-first-3-cases-all-patients-related-12331172|title=Wuhan virus: Malaysia confirms first 3 cases; all patients related to Chinese national who was Singapore's first case|website=CNA|access-date=2020-01-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200125065344/https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asia/wuhan-virus-malaysia-confirms-first-3-cases-all-patients-related-12331172|archive-date=2020-01-25|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"Malaysia25Jan\">{{cite news|url=https://www.nst.com.my/news/nation/2020/01/559563/breaking-3-coronavirus-cases-confirmed-johor-baru|title=[Breaking] 3 coronavirus cases confirmed in Johor Baru|last1=Times|first1=New Straits|date=25 January 2020|work=NST Online|accessdate=25 January 2020}}</ref> and a fourth case later.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/asia/se-asia/malaysia-confirms-first-cases-of-wuhan-coronavirus-infection|title=Wuhan virus: Malaysia confirms 4 cases, 3 patients related to Singapore's first confirmed case|last=hermesauto|date=2020-01-25|website=The Straits Times|access-date=2020-01-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200125235636/https://www.straitstimes.com/asia/se-asia/malaysia-confirms-first-cases-of-wuhan-coronavirus-infection|archive-date=2020-01-25|url-status=live}}</ref> Japan confirmed its third case.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-japan-idUSKBN1ZO08O|title=Japan confirms third case of Wuhan virus|date=2020-01-25|work=Reuters|access-date=2020-01-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200125094237/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-japan-idUSKBN1ZO08O|archive-date=2020-01-25|url-status=live}}</ref> Canada confirmed its first case in [[Toronto]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sunnybrook.ca/media/item.asp?c=1&i=2043&f=novel-coronavirus-2020|title=Patient admitted with novel coronavirus - Sunnybrook Hospital|website=sunnybrook.ca|access-date=2020-01-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200126001007/https://sunnybrook.ca/media/item.asp?c=1&i=2043&f=novel-coronavirus-2020|archive-date=2020-01-26|url-status=live}}</ref> Thailand added two new cases for a total of seven.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asia/thai-airport-virus-scans-patient-confirm-case-12338150|title=Thailand reports 7 confirmed cases of Wuhan virus, airport continues to limit temperature scans|website=CNA|access-date=2020-01-25}}</ref> Singapore confirmed their fourth case.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.moh.gov.sg/news-highlights/details/fourth-confirmed-imported-case-of-wuhan-coronavirus-infection-in-singapore|title=MOH {{!}} News Highlights|website=www.moh.gov.sg|access-date=2020-01-26}}</ref>\n\nA Chinese and a Sri Lankan suspected with the infection were admitted to a hospital in Sri Lanka.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailymirror.lk/top_story/Two-suspected-cases-of-Coronavirus-investigated-at-IDH/155-181921|title=Two suspected cases of Coronavirus investigated at IDH Sri Lanka|website=Daily Mirror|access-date=2020-01-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200125203522/http://www.dailymirror.lk/top_story/Two-suspected-cases-of-Coronavirus-investigated-at-IDH/155-181921|archive-date=2020-01-25|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nLiang Wudong, a 62-year-old doctor, reportedly died in Hubei province from the coronavirus.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://in.reuters.com/article/china-health-doctor-idINKBN1ZO04Q|title=Doctor at hospital in China's Hubei province dies from coronavirus - state media|date=2020-01-25|work=Reuters|access-date=2020-01-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200125063554/https://in.reuters.com/article/china-health-doctor-idINKBN1ZO04Q|archive-date=2020-01-25|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===26 January===\n'''WHO''' Situation Report 6:<ref>{{Citation|url=https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/situation-reports/20200126-sitrep-6-2019--ncov.pdf?sfvrsn=beaeee0c_4|title=Novel Coronavirus (2019-nCoV) Situation Report - 6 26 January 2020|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200206035857/https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/situation-reports/20200126-sitrep-6-2019--ncov.pdf?sfvrsn=beaeee0c_4|archive-date=6 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Chinese New Year|Spring Festival]] holiday was extended to contain the coronavirus outbreak.\n\n[[Shanghai]] reported its first death, an 88-year-old man.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/world-news/shanghai-reports-first-death-from-china-coronavirus-2169790|title=Shanghai Reports First Death From China Coronavirus|website=NDTV.com|access-date=2020-01-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200126035200/https://www.ndtv.com/world-news/shanghai-reports-first-death-from-china-coronavirus-2169790|archive-date=2020-01-26|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe United States confirmed its third, fourth, and fifth cases: two in [[California]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nbclosangeles.com/news/los-angeles-countys-first-case-of-deadly-novel-coronavirus-confirmed/2298402/|title=Los Angeles County's First Case of Deadly Novel Coronavirus Confirmed|website=NBC Los Angeles|access-date=2020-01-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200126191938/https://www.nbclosangeles.com/news/los-angeles-countys-first-case-of-deadly-novel-coronavirus-confirmed/2298402/|archive-date=2020-01-26|url-status=live}}</ref> and one in [[Arizona]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/summary.html|title=Novel Coronavirus 2019 Situation Summary, Wuhan, China &#124; CDC|date=29 January 2020|website=www.cdc.gov|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200126210549/https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-nCoV/summary.html|archive-date=26 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Macau confirmed three additional cases, bringing its total to five.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://macaunews.mo/government-confirms-5-cases-of-coronavirus-so-far-in-macau/|title=Government confirms 5 cases of coronavirus so far in Macau|date=2020-01-26|website=Macau News|access-date=2020-01-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200126102217/https://macaunews.mo/government-confirms-5-cases-of-coronavirus-so-far-in-macau/|archive-date=2020-01-26|url-status=live}}</ref> Hong Kong confirmed its sixth, seventh, and eighth cases.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://amp.scmp.com/news/hong-kong/health-environment/article/3047689/china-coronavirus-hong-kong-has-its-sixth-patient|title=China coronavirus-Hong Kong's sixth patient|date=2020-01-26|website=South China Morning Post}}</ref> Thailand has confirmed its eighth case. The first of five patients was already discharged. There are another 39 suspected cases awaiting confirmation.<ref name=\"Thailand26Jan2020\">{{cite news|url=https://www.pptvhd36.com/news/\u0e1b\u0e23\u0e30\u0e40\u0e14\u0e47\u0e19\u0e23\u0e49\u0e2d\u0e19/118387|title=\u0e2a\u0e18.\u0e22\u0e37\u0e19\u0e22\u0e31\u0e19\u0e1e\u0e1a\u0e1c\u0e39\u0e49\u0e1b\u0e48\u0e27\u0e22 \"\u0e44\u0e27\u0e23\u0e31\u0e2a\u0e42\u0e04\u0e42\u0e23\u0e19\u0e32\" 8 \u0e23\u0e32\u0e22|date=25 January 2020|accessdate=26 January 2020|language=th|website=PPTVHD36}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Chinese Center for Disease Control and Prevention]] (CCDC) has started developing vaccines against the coronavirus, an official with the center said on Sunday.<ref name=\":8\">{{cite web|url=https://www.scmp.com/news/china/society/article/3047676/number-coronavirus-cases-china-doubles-spread-rate-accelerates|title=Chinese scientists race to develop vaccine as coronavirus death toll jumps|date=2020-01-26|website=SCMP|access-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200126073453/https://www.scmp.com/news/china/society/article/3047676/number-coronavirus-cases-china-doubles-spread-rate-accelerates|archive-date=2020-01-26|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"xinhua_vacc\">{{cite web|url=http://www.xinhuanet.com/english/2020-01/26/c_138734908.htm|title=China CDC developing novel coronavirus vaccine|date=2020-01-26|website=Xinhua|access-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200126201658/http://www.xinhuanet.com/english/2020-01/26/c_138734908.htm|archive-date=2020-01-26|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nHealth officials in Ivory Coast are dealing with a suspected case of coronavirus, the country's health ministry has announced.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-51258014|title=Ivory Coast fears China virus has reached Africa|date=2020-01-26|work=BBC News|access-date=2020-01-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200128004440/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-51258014|archive-date=2020-01-28|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe United Nation's [[World Health Organization|WHO]] Director-General [[Tedros Adhanom|Tedros Ghebreyesus]] said he was on his way to Beijing to confer with Chinese officials and health experts about the coronavirus outbreak.<ref name=\"reuters26jan\">{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-who-idUSKBN1ZP0OG|title=WHO chief says he is on way to China to confer on virus, boost response|date=2020-01-26|work=Reuters|access-date=2020-01-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200126185333/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-who-idUSKBN1ZP0OG|archive-date=2020-01-26|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nChina started requiring nationwide use of monitoring stations for screening, identification and immediate isolation of coronavirus-infected travellers, including at airports, railway stations, bus stations and ports.<ref name=\"china_measures\">{{cite web|url=https://news.yahoo.com/china-orders-nationwide-measures-detect-virus-flights-trains-090541811.html|title=China orders nationwide measures to detect virus on flights, trains, buses|website=news.yahoo.com|access-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200126235511/https://news.yahoo.com/china-orders-nationwide-measures-detect-virus-flights-trains-090541811.html|archive-date=2020-01-26|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nA [https://foreignpolicy.com/2020/01/26/2019-ncov-china-epidemic-pandemic-the-wuhan-coronavirus-a-tentative-clinical-profile tentative clinical profile for the new coronavirus (2019-nCoV)] was published by an assistant professor of population health science at the [[Icahn School of Medicine at Mount Sinai]] in New York. The lethality of the virus is unknown; however, the death toll has now climbed to above three percent.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://foreignpolicy.com/2020/01/26/2019-ncov-china-epidemic-pandemic-the-wuhan-coronavirus-a-tentative-clinical-profile/|title=How China's Coronavirus Is Spreading\u2014and How to Stop It|first=Annie|last=Sparrow|access-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200131025848/https://foreignpolicy.com/2020/01/26/2019-ncov-china-epidemic-pandemic-the-wuhan-coronavirus-a-tentative-clinical-profile/|archive-date=2020-01-31|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nWang Xianliang, a Hubei provincial government official, died of pneumonia caused by the virus.<ref name=\"Radio Free Asia\"/>\n\n===27 January===\n'''WHO''' Situation Report 7:<ref>{{Citation|url=https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/situation-reports/20200127-sitrep-7-2019--ncov.pdf?sfvrsn=98ef79f5_2|title=Novel Coronavirus(2019-nCoV) Situation Report - 7|access-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200131215148/https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/situation-reports/20200127-sitrep-7-2019--ncov.pdf?sfvrsn=98ef79f5_2|archive-date=2020-01-31|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nGabriel Leung, Dean of the University of Hong Kong medical school and one of the foremost world experts on SARS and viruses, gave a three-hour presentation published on YouTube wherein he made nowcasts and forecasts of the coronavirus. Using traditional scientific modeling techniques that predict the spread of viruses, Leung projected the true number of coronavirus infections was likely 10 time more than the official reported numbers.<ref>{{Citation|title=Dr Gabriel Leung Dean of Medicine dire projection|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CwXMPsbxFfo|language=en|access-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200201190644/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CwXMPsbxFfo|archive-date=2020-02-01|url-status=live}}</ref> Leung estimated that there were between 44,000\u2013100,000 infections in China as of 24 January 2020. He stated that draconian measures were needed to slow the progress of the virus but that these measures would have no effect in stopping the coronavirus pandemic. He projected that the number of infections would continue exponentially peaking out in late April or May 2020. Leung predicted that at the peak of the pandemic, there could be up to 100,000 new infections per day. Leung subsequently published an article in The Lancet nowcasting and forecasting the likely progression of the Wuhan coronavirus taking into consideration numerous variables.<ref>{{Cite journal|url=https://www.thelancet.com/journals/lancet/article/PIIS0140-6736(20)30260-9/abstract|title=Nowcasting and forecasting the potential domestic and international spread of the 2019-nCoV outbreak originating in Wuhan, China: a modelling study|first1=Joseph T.|last1=Wu|first2=Kathy|last2=Leung|first3=Gabriel M.|last3=Leung|date=31 January 2020|journal=The Lancet|volume=0|issue=10225|pages=689\u2013697|doi=10.1016/S0140-6736(20)30260-9|pmid=32014114}}</ref>\nZhou Xianwang, the mayor of Wuhan, said on a Chinese state television talkshow that rules imposed by Beijing limited what he could disclose about the threat posed by the Wuhan coronavirus as it unfolded, suggesting \"the central government was partially responsible for a lack of transparency that has marred the response to the fast-expanding health crisis.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinas-premier-tours-virus-epicenter-as-anger-bubbles-at-crisis-response-11580109098|title=Wuhan Mayor Says Beijing Rules Partially Responsible for Lack of Transparency|first=Josh|last=Chin|date=28 January 2020|via=www.wsj.com|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200207052922/https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinas-premier-tours-virus-epicenter-as-anger-bubbles-at-crisis-response-11580109098|archive-date=7 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nCanada reported its first confirmed case and another presumptive case.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://news.ontario.ca/mohltc/en/2020/01/ontario-confirms-second-presumptive-case-of-wuhan-novel-coronavirus.html|title=Ontario Confirms Second Presumptive Case of Wuhan Novel Coronavirus|date=2020-01-27|work=Queen's Printer for Ontario|access-date=2020-01-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200127133734/https://news.ontario.ca/mohltc/en/2020/01/ontario-confirms-second-presumptive-case-of-wuhan-novel-coronavirus.html|archive-date=2020-01-27|url-status=live}}</ref> Health officials have confirmed the fifth case of coronavirus in Australia, and have suspected an additional 5.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://7news.com.au/lifestyle/health-wellbeing/coronavirus-confirmed-fifth-australian-case-21-year-old-infected-with-deadly-virus--c-666385|title=Australia's fifth coronavirus case confirmed as death toll rises|date=2020-01-27|website=7NEWS.com.au|access-date=2020-01-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200127045226/https://7news.com.au/lifestyle/health-wellbeing/coronavirus-confirmed-fifth-australian-case-21-year-old-infected-with-deadly-virus--c-666385|archive-date=2020-01-27|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theaustralian.com.au/subscribe/news/1/?sourceCode=TAWEB_WRE170_a&dest=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theaustralian.com.au%