27/https://www.newshub.co.nz/home/world/2020/01/pacific-nations-on-alert-for-coronavirus-6-quarantined-in-fiji.html|archive-date=2020-01-27|url-status=live}}</ref> In Poland, two children were admitted to the [[Krak\u00f3w]] hospital with the suspicion of coronavirus.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://krakow.wyborcza.pl/krakow/7,44425,25638900,do-krakowskiego-szpita-trafilo-dwoje-dzieci-z-podejrzeniem-koronawirusa.html|language=pl|website=krakow.wyborcza.pl|access-date=2020-01-27|date=2020-01-27|title=Dwoje dzieci ze \u015al\u0105ska trafi\u0142o na dzieci\u0119cy oddzia\u0142 zaka\u017any krakowskiego szpitala im. \u017beromskiego. Wraz z rodzicami wraca\u0142y przez Pekin do kraju i zachorowa\u0142y|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200127182321/https://krakow.wyborcza.pl/krakow/7,44425,25638900,do-krakowskiego-szpita-trafilo-dwoje-dzieci-z-podejrzeniem-koronawirusa.html|archive-date=2020-01-27|url-status=live}}</ref> In Mongolia a 14-year-old girl who was studying in China had fallen ill with a suspected case of pneumonia and laryngitis; she was pronounced dead on the same day. Health authorities have since taken a sample from the deceased girl to be analysed at the National Center for Communicable Diseases in [[Ulaanbaatar]].<ref name=\"auto3\">{{cite web|url=https://ikon.mn/n/1s32|title=\u0425\u044d\u043d\u0442\u0438\u0439 \u0430\u0439\u043c\u0433\u0438\u0439\u043d \u044d\u043c\u043d\u044d\u043b\u044d\u0433\u0442 \u043d\u0430\u0441 \u0431\u0430\u0440\u0441\u0430\u043d \u043e\u0445\u0438\u043d\u044b \u0446\u043e\u0433\u0446\u0441\u043e\u043e\u0441 \u0441\u043e\u0440\u044c\u0446 \u0430\u0432\u0447, \u0434\u044d\u044d\u0436\u0438\u0439\u0433 \u0425\u04e8\u0421\u04ae\u0422-\u0434 \u0438\u043b\u0433\u044d\u044d\u0441\u044d\u043d|last=iKon.mn|first=\u0413. \u04e8\u043b\u0437\u0438\u0439\u0445\u0443\u0442\u0430\u0433|date=2020-01-27|website=ikon.mn|access-date=2020-01-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200127155037/https://ikon.mn/n/1s32|archive-date=2020-01-27|url-status=live}}</ref> Two Mongolian students returning from Taiwan to [[Chinggis Khaan International Airport]] have shown symptoms of high fever and rising temperature and were put into quarantine after landing in Mongolia.<ref name=\"auto3\"/> In Switzerland, two people were put under quarantine at the [[Triemli Hospital]] in Zurich; both had previously been to China.<ref>{{citation|url=https://www.srf.ch/news/international/corona-virus-auf-dem-vormarsch-verdachtsfaelle-in-der-schweiz-gemeldet|date=2020-01-27|language=de|access-date=2020-01-27|title=Verdachtsf\u00e4lle in der Schweiz gemeldet|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200126220817/https://www.srf.ch/news/international/corona-virus-auf-dem-vormarsch-verdachtsfaelle-in-der-schweiz-gemeldet|archive-date=2020-01-26|url-status=live}}</ref> These cases later turned up negative.<ref>{{citation|url=https://www.swissinfo.ch/eng/coronavirus_swiss-tighten-rules-to-help-stop-spread-of-china-virus/45518156|date=2020-01-27|language=en|access-date=2020-01-27|title=Two quarantined patients do not have coronavirus, confirms Zurich hospital|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200127015652/https://www.swissinfo.ch/eng/coronavirus_swiss-tighten-rules-to-help-stop-spread-of-china-virus/45518156|archive-date=2020-01-27|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn [[Germany]], the first specific, global case of coronavirus being transmitted by a person with no symptoms has been reported. The originally-infected individual is from [[Shanghai]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sciencenews.org/article/first-case-coronavirus-spread-person-no-symptoms-found-germany|title=The first case of coronavirus being spread by a person with no symptoms has been found|first=Tina Hesman|last=Saey|date=31 January 2020|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200203054720/https://www.sciencenews.org/article/first-case-coronavirus-spread-person-no-symptoms-found-germany|archive-date=3 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/study-reports-first-case-of-coronavirus-spread-by-asymptomatic-person/|title=Study Reports First Case of Coronavirus Spread By Asymptomatic Person|first=Andrew|last=Joseph,STAT|website=Scientific American|access-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200205163704/https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/study-reports-first-case-of-coronavirus-spread-by-asymptomatic-person/|archive-date=2020-02-05|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.statnews.com/2020/01/30/first-documented-case-of-coronavirus-spread-by-person-showing-no-symptoms/|title=First case of coronavirus spread by a person showing no symptoms|date=31 January 2020|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200205163743/https://www.statnews.com/2020/01/30/first-documented-case-of-coronavirus-spread-by-person-showing-no-symptoms/|archive-date=5 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=Transmission of 2019-nCoV Infection from an Asymptomatic Contact in Germany|first1=Camilla|last1=Rothe|first2=Mirjam|last2=Schunk|first3=Peter|last3=Sothmann|first4=Gisela|last4=Bretzel|first5=Guenter|last5=Froeschl|first6=Claudia|last6=Wallrauch|first7=Thorbj\u00f6rn|last7=Zimmer|first8=Verena|last8=Thiel|first9=Christian|last9=Janke|first10=Wolfgang|last10=Guggemos|first11=Michael|last11=Seilmaier|first12=Christian|last12=Drosten |author-link12=Christian Drosten|first13=Patrick|last13=Vollmar|first14=Katrin|last14=Zwirglmaier|first15=Sabine|last15=Zange|first16=Roman|last16=W\u00f6lfel|first17=Michael|last17=Hoelscher|date=30 January 2020|journal=New England Journal of Medicine|volume=0|issue=10|pages=970\u2013971|doi=10.1056/NEJMc2001468|pmid= 32003551}}</ref>\n\nSouth Korean health officials met with Korean life science company representatives to speed the development of a test.<ref>Chad Terhune, Dan Levine, Hyunjoo Jin, and Jane Lanhee Lee. (18 March 2020). \"Special Report: How Korea trounced U.S. in race to test people for coronavirus\". [https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-testing-specialrep-idUSKBN2153BW Reuters website] Retrieved 21 March 2020.</ref>\n\n===28 January===\nChina's Supreme People's Court through a message \u300a\u6cbb\u7406\u6709\u5173\u65b0\u578b\u80ba\u708e\u7684\u8c23\u8a00\u95ee\u9898\uff0c\u8fd9\u7bc7\u6587\u7ae0\u8bf4\u6e05\u695a\u4e86\uff01\u300bin its official WeChat account vindicated Dr. Li [[Li Wenliang|Wenliang]] and the other 7 doctors and said they should not have been punished as what they said was not entirely false.<ref name=\"web.archive.org\" /><ref name=\":3\">{{cite web|url=https://asia.nikkei.com/Spotlight/Caixin/Rebuked-coronavirus-whistleblower-vindicated-by-top-Chinese-court|title=Rebuked coronavirus whistleblower vindicated by top Chinese court|website=Nikkei Asian Review|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref> The Court further stated that  \"based on the difference in cognitive level, different individuals may produce different degrees of false information about the same thing. We should permit the law's to have certain degree of tolerance towards individuals. For example, in the case of the 8 persons being punished by Wuhan Police for publishing \"7 SARS cases diagnosed in the Huanan Seafood Market\u201d, if we mechanically applying the law, since the new coronavirus infected pneumonia is not SARS, by saying SARS has emerged we can indeed determine that is fabrication of false information, and the information has caused chaos in the social order. In accordance with the law provided, administrative punishment and even criminal punishment can be justified for the act of fabricating and disseminating false information. However, the fact is the message is not entirely false. If society had at the time believed those 'rumours', and wore masks, used disinfectant and avoided going to the wildlife market as if there were a SARS outbreak, perhaps it will help us better control the coronavirus today\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.caixinglobal.com/2020-01-31/after-being-punished-by-local-police-coronavirus-whistleblower-vindicated-by-top-court-101509986.html|title=Whistleblower Li Wenliang: There Should Be More Than One Voice In A Healthy Society|website=www.caixinglobal.com|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200205002435/https://www.caixinglobal.com/2020-01-31/after-being-punished-by-local-police-coronavirus-whistleblower-vindicated-by-top-court-101509986.html|archive-date=2020-02-05|access-date=2020-02-08}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/ETgXN6HInzlC8cxzhDdU9g|publisher=[[Supreme People's Court]]|script-title=zh:\u6cbb\u7406\u6709\u5173\u65b0\u578b\u80ba\u708e\u7684\u8c23\u8a00\u95ee\u9898\uff0c\u8fd9\u7bc7\u6587\u7ae0\u8bf4\u6e05\u695a\u4e86!|trans-title=Regarding the issue of authorities handling the new novel coronavirus as rumours|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200202004701/https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/ETgXN6HInzlC8cxzhDdU9g|archive-date=2020-02-02|access-date=2020-02-08}}</ref>\n\n'''WHO''' Situation Report 8:<ref>{{Citation|url=https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/situation-reports/20200128-sitrep-8-ncov-cleared.pdf?sfvrsn=8b671ce5_2|title=Novel Coronavirus(2019-nCoV) Situation Report - 8|access-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200202195554/https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/situation-reports/20200128-sitrep-8-ncov-cleared.pdf?sfvrsn=8b671ce5_2|archive-date=2020-02-02|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThailand confirms six more cases, bringing the total infected there to 14. Thailand's health minister, [[Anutin Charnvirakul]], states that \"we are not able to stop the spread\" of coronavirus in the country.<ref name=\"auto11\">{{cite web|url=https://news.sky.com/story/thailand-not-able-to-stop-the-spread-of-new-coronavirus-11919860|title=Thailand 'not able to stop the spread' of new coronavirus|website=Sky News|access-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200202160111/https://news.sky.com/story/thailand-not-able-to-stop-the-spread-of-new-coronavirus-11919860|archive-date=2020-02-02|url-status=live}}</ref> Singapore confirms two more cases, bringing the total infected in Singapore to seven. That was followed by a Hubei-related suspension from 29 January.<ref name=\"auto2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/wuhan-virus-7-confirmed-cases-in-singapore-no-entry-or-transit-for-new-visitors-with-hubei|title=Wuhan virus: 2 new confirmed cases in Singapore, bringing total to 7; no entry or transit for new visitors from Hubei|website=The Straits Times|accessdate=28 January 2020|date=28 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200128094942/https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/wuhan-virus-7-confirmed-cases-in-singapore-no-entry-or-transit-for-new-visitors-with-hubei|archive-date=28 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Japan confirms 3 additional cases, bringing the total infected in Japan to seven, including a man who had never visited Wuhan. He was working as a tour bus driver and had driven a group from Wuhan earlier in January.<ref name=\"auto8\">{{cite web|url=https://english.kyodonews.net/news/2020/01/e8f47252a245-urgent-japan-sees-1st-coronavirus-case-not-linked-to-recent-travel-to-china.html|title=Japan sees 1st coronavirus case not linked to recent travel to China|date=28 January 2020|via=Kyodo News|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200129162636/https://english.kyodonews.net/news/2020/01/e8f47252a245-urgent-japan-sees-1st-coronavirus-case-not-linked-to-recent-travel-to-china.html|archive-date=29 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"auto10\">{{cite web|url=https://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2020/01/28/national/japan-charter-flights-evacuate-japanese-virus-wuhan-china/#.XjAFCLdlB-E|title=Japan reports new coronavirus cases as it moves to evacuate nationals from Wuhan|date=28 January 2020|via=The Japan Times|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200128134009/https://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2020/01/28/national/japan-charter-flights-evacuate-japanese-virus-wuhan-china/#.XjAFCLdlB-E|archive-date=28 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Germany's first confirmed case, reported the previous day, had occurred in a German citizen who had not travelled to China. However, he had close contact with a visiting Chinese colleague who reported starting to feel ill during her return flight to Shanghai and she was diagnosed with coronavirus infection after arriving in China. Germany confirmed 3 new cases, all of whom were coworkers of the first confirmed patient.<ref name=\"auto6\">{{cite web|url=https://www.sueddeutsche.de/gesundheit/coronavirus-drei-weitere-infizierte-in-bayern-1.4776016|title=Drei weitere Infizierte in Bayern|last=Zeitung|first=S\u00fcddeutsche|website=S\u00fcddeutsche.de|language=de|access-date=2020-01-28}}</ref> France confirmed its fourth case, an elderly Chinese tourist who is in critical condition.<ref name=\"auto5\">{{cite web|url=https://www.france24.com/fr/20200128-nouveau-coronavirus-quatri%C3%A8me-cas-en-france-le-patient-en-r%C3%A9animation|title=Quatri\u00e8me cas en France, le patient en r\u00e9animation|last=|first=|date=|website=Franceinfo|language=fr|access-date=2020-01-28}}</ref>\n\nThe Brazilian [[Ministry of Health (Brazil)|Ministry of Health]] reports three suspected cases ongoing in three locations: [[Belo Horizonte]] (MG), [[Curitiba]] (PR) and [[S\u00e3o Leopoldo]] (RS).<ref name=\"auto7\">{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/ciencia-e-saude/noticia/2020/01/28/brasil-tem-2-novos-casos-suspeitos-de-coronavirus-em-porto-alegre-e-curitiba-ministerio.ghtml|title=Brasil tem 2 novos casos suspeitos de coronav\u00edrus em S\u00e3o Leopoldo e em Curitiba, diz Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade|website=G1|access-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200131042625/https://g1.globo.com/ciencia-e-saude/noticia/2020/01/28/brasil-tem-2-novos-casos-suspeitos-de-coronavirus-em-porto-alegre-e-curitiba-ministerio.ghtml|archive-date=2020-01-31|url-status=live}}</ref> Canada reports a new presumptive case in [[British Columbia]], a man in his 40s who had recently travelled to Wuhan.<ref name=\"auto12\">{{cite web|url=https://globalnews.ca/news/6473048/bc-coronavirus-update-tuesday-jan-28/|title=First presumptive case of coronavirus confirmed in B.C.|website=Global News|language=en|access-date=2020-01-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200128183227/https://globalnews.ca/news/6473048/bc-coronavirus-update-tuesday-jan-28/|archive-date=2020-01-28|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nA UK-Chinese medical research paper reports a statistical model finding that \"estimates suggest the actual number of infected cases could be much higher than the reported, with estimated 26,701 cases (as of 28th January 2020).\"<ref>{{cite journal|url=https://www.biorxiv.org/content/10.1101/2020.01.27.922443v1|title=Breaking down of the healthcare system: Mathematical modelling for controlling the novel coronavirus (2019-nCoV) outbreak in Wuhan, China|first1=Wai-kit|last1=Ming|first2=Jian|last2=Huang|first3=Casper J. P.|last3=Zhang|date=28 January 2020|journal=bioRxiv|pages=2020.01.27.922443|via=www.biorxiv.org|doi=10.1101/2020.01.27.922443|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200201160242/https://www.biorxiv.org/content/10.1101/2020.01.27.922443v1|archive-date=1 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nScientists from The Peter Doherty Institute for Infection and Immunity (Doherty Institute) in Melbourne reported that they had successfully grown 2019-nCoV from a patient sample.<ref name=\"auto9\">{{cite web|url=https://www.doherty.edu.au/news-events/news/coronavirus|title=Doherty Institute scientists first to grow and share Wuhan coronavirus|last=|first=|date=|website=www.doherty.edu.au|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200128203302/https://www.doherty.edu.au/news-events/news/coronavirus|archive-date=2020-01-28|access-date=2020-01-28}}</ref>\n\n[[Xiangyang]] became quarantined starting 00:00;<ref name=\":101\">{{cite web|url=https://www.thepaper.cn/newsDetail_forward_5671283|title=\u8944\u9633\u706b\u8f66\u7ad9\u5173\u95ed\uff0c\u6e56\u5317\u7701\u6700\u540e\u4e00\u4e2a\u5730\u7ea7\u5e02\"\u5c01\u57ce\"_\u5a92\u4f53_\u6f8e\u6e43\u65b0\u95fb-The Paper|website=www.thepaper.cn|access-date=2020-02-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200202170024/https://www.thepaper.cn/newsDetail_forward_5671283|archive-date=2020-02-02|url-status=live}}</ref> the entire Hubei province thus became quarantined save for [[Shennongjia Forestry District]].\n\n===29 January===\n'''WHO''' Situation Report 9:<ref name=\"auto13\">{{Citation|url=https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/situation-reports/20200129-sitrep-9-ncov-v2.pdf?sfvrsn=e2c8915_2|title=Novel Coronavirus(2019-nCoV) Situation Report - 9|access-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200206035856/https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/situation-reports/20200129-sitrep-9-ncov-v2.pdf?sfvrsn=e2c8915_2|archive-date=2020-02-06|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n[[Tibet Autonomous Region|Tibet]] reported its first suspected case identified on the previous day<ref name=\"sina_tibet\">{{cite web|url=https://news.sina.com.cn/c/2020-01-29/doc-iihnzhha5188508.shtml|title=\u897f\u85cf\u65b0\u589e\u65b0\u578b\u51a0\u72b6\u75c5\u6bd2\u80ba\u708e1\u4f8b\u7591\u4f3c\u75c5\u4f8b|last=\u4eba\u6c11\u65e5\u62a5|date=2020-01-29|website=news.sina.com.cn|access-date=2020-01-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200129034117/https://news.sina.com.cn/c/2020-01-29/doc-iihnzhha5188508.shtml|archive-date=2020-01-29|url-status=live}}</ref> and declared a level 1 health emergency in the evening, the last mainland provincial division to do so.<ref name=\"tibet_emer\">{{cite web|url=https://jiemian.com/article/3924819.html|title=\u897f\u85cf\u542f\u52a8\u91cd\u5927\u7a81\u53d1\u516c\u5171\u536b\u751f\u4e8b\u4ef6\u2160\u7ea7\u54cd\u5e94{{!}}\u754c\u9762\u65b0\u95fb \u00b7 \u5feb\u8baf|last=|first=|date=|website=jiemian.com|access-date=2020-01-29}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}{{Dead link|date=February 2020|bot=InternetArchiveBot|fix-attempted=yes}}</ref> Suspected cases have now been reported in all 31 mainland provincial divisions.\n\nCompanies in Hubei are required not to resume services before 13 February, and schools in Hubei are to postpone the reopening of schools.<ref name=\":14\">{{cite web|url=http://cnhubei.com/content/2020-01/29/content_12659024.html|title=\u6e56\u5317\u7701\u5404\u7c7b\u4f01\u4e1a\u590d\u5de5\u65f6\u95f4\u4e0d\u65e9\u4e8e2\u670813\u65e524\u65f6|language=zh|date=2020-01-29|website=cnhubei.com|accessdate=2020-01-29}}</ref>\n\nThe [[United Arab Emirates|UAE]] confirms its first case.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://gulfnews.com/uae/health/coronavirus-first-case-confirmed-in-uae-1.1580273983681|title=Coronavirus: First case confirmed in UAE|website=gulfnews.com|accessdate=2020-01-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200129051659/https://gulfnews.com/uae/health/coronavirus-first-case-confirmed-in-uae-1.1580273983681|archive-date=2020-01-29|url-status=live}}</ref> Shortly afterwards, an [[Emirates (airline)|Emirates]]' news agency confirmed four people from a Chinese family to be infected.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://gulfnews.com/uae/health/coronavirus-in-uae-four-of-a-family-infected-1.1580273983681|title=Coronavirus in UAE: Four of a family infected|website=gulfnews.com|accessdate=2020-01-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200129111625/https://gulfnews.com/uae/health/coronavirus-in-uae-four-of-a-family-infected-1.1580273983681|archive-date=2020-01-29|url-status=live}}</ref> Finland reports its first case of the virus in [[Lapland (Finland)|Lapland]], found in a Chinese tourist who left Wuhan before Wuhan was locked down.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://yle.fi/uutiset/osasto/news/finlands_first_coronavirus_case_confirmed_in_lapland/11182855|title=Finland's first coronavirus case confirmed in Lapland|date=2020-01-29|publisher=YLE|location=Finland|accessdate=2020-01-30}}</ref> Singapore confirms three more cases of the virus, bringing the total infected to 10.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/wuhan-virus-singapore-new-confirmed-cases-coronavirus-12364556|title=Singapore confirms 3 new cases of Wuhan virus; total of 10 infected|accessdate=2020-01-29|website=CNA|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200129112711/https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/wuhan-virus-singapore-new-confirmed-cases-coronavirus-12364556|archive-date=2020-01-29|url-status=live}}</ref> Malaysia confirms three additional cases, bringing its total to seven.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nst.com.my/news/nation/2020/01/560544/three-more-positive-coronavirus-cases-malaysia-bringing-total-7|title=Three more positive coronavirus cases in Malaysia, bringing total to 7|publisher=New Straits Times|date=2020-01-29|url-status=live|accessdate=2020-01-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200129012136/https://www.nst.com.my/news/nation/2020/01/560544/three-more-positive-coronavirus-cases-malaysia-bringing-total-7|archive-date=2020-01-29}}</ref> Japan reports four additional cases, including a tour bus guide that was on the same bus as one of the cases confirmed on 28 January<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www3.nhk.or.jp/news/html/20200129/k10012264621000.html|title=\u30d0\u30b9\u3067\u30ac\u30a4\u30c9 \u5927\u962a\u306e\u5973\u6027 \u30a6\u30a4\u30eb\u30b9\u306b\u611f\u67d3 \u5948\u826f\u306e\u904b\u8ee2\u624b\u3068\u540c\u4e57|last=\u65e5\u672c\u653e\u9001\u5354\u4f1a|language=Japanese|location=Japan|publisher=NHK\u30cb\u30e5\u30fc\u30b9|accessdate=2020-01-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200129123513/https://www3.nhk.or.jp/news/html/20200129/k10012264621000.html|archive-date=2020-01-29|url-status=live}}</ref> and three evacuated from Wuhan.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www3.nhk.or.jp/news/html/20200130/k10012264981000.html|title=\u65b0\u578b\u80ba\u708e 29\u65e5\u5e30\u56fd\u306e\uff13\u4eba\u611f\u67d3\u78ba\u8a8d \u3046\u30612\u4eba\u306f\u767a\u71b1\u306a\u3069\u75c7\u72b6\u306a\u3057|website=NHK\u30cb\u30e5\u30fc\u30b9|access-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130235311/https://www3.nhk.or.jp/news/html/20200130/k10012264981000.html|archive-date=2020-01-30|url-status=live}}</ref> France confirmed a fifth case, the daughter of the patient in the fourth case.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bfmtv.com/sante/coronavirus-en-france-un-cinquieme-cas-confirme-la-fille-du-touriste-chinois-hospitalise-a-paris-1849280.html|title=Coronavirus en France: un cinqui\u00e8me cas confirm\u00e9, la fille du touriste chinois hospitalis\u00e9 \u00e0 Paris|language=French|trans-title=Coronavirus in France: A fith case confirmed, the daughter of a Chinese tourist hospitalised in Paris|work=BFM TV|date=29 January 2020|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130195933/https://www.bfmtv.com/sante/coronavirus-en-france-un-cinquieme-cas-confirme-la-fille-du-touriste-chinois-hospitalise-a-paris-1849280.html|archive-date=30 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nTwo Chinese nationals were placed in isolation wards in [[Armenia]] amid the first suspected case of coronavirus in the country. The Chinese nationals were tourists travelling to Armenia from neighbouring [[Georgia (country)|Georgia]]. Liana Torosyan, the head of the Department of Infectious Diseases, advised that samples will be sent to European labs, as Armenia does not have the capacity to test for the novel coronavirus.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://armenpress.am/eng/news/1002962.html|title=Two Chinese nationals placed in isolation wards in Armenia amid first suspected case of coronavirus|date=29 January 2020|website=Armenpress.am|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200201155551/https://armenpress.am/eng/news/1002962.html|archive-date=1 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Brazil reports a total of 9 suspected cases in six states of the country.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/01/29/brasil-tem-nove-casos-suspeitos-de-coronavirus-e-33-notificacoes.ghtml|title=Brasil tem 9 casos suspeitos de coronav\u00edrus em 6 estados|publisher=O Globo|location=Brazil|language=Portuguese|website=G1|access-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200129210423/https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/01/29/brasil-tem-nove-casos-suspeitos-de-coronavirus-e-33-notificacoes.ghtml|archive-date=2020-01-29|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nAir Canada is halting all direct flights to China following the federal government's advisory to avoid non-essential travel to the mainland due to the coronavirus epidemic. The suspension is effective Thursday and slated to last until February 29.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://vancouverisland.ctvnews.ca/air-canada-suspends-all-direct-flights-to-china-as-coronavirus-spreads-1.4789002|title=Air Canada suspends all direct flights to China as coronavirus spreads|date=29 January 2020|website=Vancouver Island|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200201014048/https://vancouverisland.ctvnews.ca/air-canada-suspends-all-direct-flights-to-china-as-coronavirus-spreads-1.4789002|archive-date=1 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nTrump administration trade advisor [[Peter Navarro]] issued a memo warning that coronavirus could \"evolv[e] into a full-blown pandemic, imperiling the lives of millions of Americans\" and that the \"risk of a worst-case pandemic scenario should not be overlooked\". A critic of the Chinese government before the pandemic, Navarro argued for restrictions on travel from China.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Haberman |first1=Maggie |title=Trade Adviser Warned White House in January of Risks of a Pandemic |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/04/06/us/politics/navarro-warning-trump-coronavirus.html?action=click&module=Spotlight&pgtype=Homepage |accessdate=7 April 2020 |work=The New York Times |date=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe Wuhan police clarified that Dr. Li Wenliang was not arrested nor fined, but was warned as he had spread that \"there had been 7 confirmed cases of SARS\", which was not true.<ref name=\"weibo1\" /> \n\n===30 January===\n'''WHO''' Situation Report 10:<ref>{{Citation|url=https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/situation-reports/20200130-sitrep-10-ncov.pdf?sfvrsn=d0b2e480_2|title=Novel Coronavirus(2019-nCoV) Situation Report - 10|access-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200131005409/https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/situation-reports/20200130-sitrep-10-ncov.pdf|archive-date=2020-01-31|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nTibet confirms its first case, which was previously suspected.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://wjw.xizang.gov.cn/xwzx/wsjkdt/202001/t20200130_131185.html|title=\u897f\u85cf\u81ea\u6cbb\u533a\u786e\u8bca\u9996\u4f8b\u65b0\u578b\u51a0\u72b6\u75c5\u6bd2\u611f\u67d3\u7684\u80ba\u708e\u75c5\u4f8b_\u897f\u85cf\u81ea\u6cbb\u533a\u536b\u751f\u5065\u5eb7\u59d4\u5458\u4f1a|website=wjw.xizang.gov.cn|access-date=2020-01-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130000144/http://wjw.xizang.gov.cn/xwzx/wsjkdt/202001/t20200130_131185.html|archive-date=2020-01-30|url-status=live}}</ref> Cases have now been confirmed in all 31 provincial divisions of mainland China.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-china-51305526|title=Coronavirus: Death toll rises as virus spreads to every Chinese region|website=bbc.co.uk|access-date=2020-01-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130030316/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-china-51305526|archive-date=2020-01-30|url-status=live}}</ref> India confirms its first case of coronavirus in a student who had returned from [[Wuhan University]] to the Indian state of [[Kerala]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Kerala reports first confirmed coronavirus case in India|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/kerala-reports-first-confirmed-novel-coronavirus-case-in-india-1641593-2020-01-30|accessdate=30 January 2020|publisher=indiatoday.com|location=India|date=30 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130082158/https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/kerala-reports-first-confirmed-novel-coronavirus-case-in-india-1641593-2020-01-30|archive-date=30 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Philippines confirms its first case of coronavirus in a female Chinese national who arrived in [[Manila]] via [[Hong Kong]] on 21 January.<ref>{{cite news|title=Philippines confirms first case of novel coronavirus|url=https://cnnphilippines.com/news/2020/1/30/Philippines-coronavirus-case.html|accessdate=30 January 2020|publisher=cnnphilippines.com|location=Philippines|date=30 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130090313/https://www.cnnphilippines.com/news/2020/1/30/Philippines-coronavirus-case.html|archive-date=30 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\nJapan confirms three more cases, bringing the total to 14.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www3.nhk.or.jp/news/html/20200130/k10012266331000.html|title=\u65b0\u578b\u80ba\u708e \u56fd\u5185\u611f\u67d3\u800514\u4eba\u306b \u65b0\u305f\u306b\u7537\u5973\uff13\u4eba\u611f\u67d3\u78ba\u8a8d|date=2020-01-30|website=NHK|access-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200201165246/https://www3.nhk.or.jp/news/html/20200130/k10012266331000.html?utm_int=news-new_contents_list-items_091|archive-date=2020-02-01|url-status=live}}</ref>\nMalaysia confirms one more case, bringing the total to eight.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nst.com.my/news/nation/2020/01/560955/another-chinese-national-tests-positive-2019-ncov|title=Another Chinese national tests positive for 2019-nCoV|last=Harun|first=Hana Naz|date=2020-01-30|website=NST Onli